xt":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Oct. 30, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/591/tVI/s6010"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–591, title VI, § 6010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3341-388"},"text":"100 Stat. 3341–388","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a), before clause (1), the text of section 6005(a) and (d) of the Metropolitan Washington Airports Act of 1986 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/500"},"text":"Public Law 99–500","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/1783-375"},"text":"100 Stat. 1783–375","children":[],"tail":", 1783–378, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/591"},"text":"Public Law 99–591","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3341-378"},"text":"100 Stat. 3341–378","children":[],"tail":", 3341–381) is omitted as executed. The words “conditions and requirements” are omitted as surplus. In clause (5)(B), the words “(relating to new-technology aircraft)” and “(relating to violations of Federal Aviation Administration regulations as Federal misdemeanors)” are omitted as surplus. In clause (5)(C), the words “after the date the lease takes effect” are omitted as obsolete. In clause (6)(A), the words “(tangible and incorporeal, present and executory)” are omitted as surplus. The words “The Airports Authority must” are substituted for “Before the date the lease takes effect, the Secretary shall also assure that the Airports Authority has agreed to” to eliminate obsolete words. The words “duties and powers” are substituted for “functions” for consistency in the revised title and with other titles of the United States Code. In clause (7), the words “or places” are omitted because of 1:1. The words “books, accounts . . . reports, files, papers” are omitted as being included in “reports”. In clause (8), the words “for purposes of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s49106/d"},"text":"section 49106(d) of this title","children":[],"tail":"” are added for clarity. In clause (9), before subclause (A), the words “Notwithstanding any other provision of law” are omitted as surplus. In clause (11), the words “and conditions” are omitted as being included in “terms”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b), the text of section 6005(b)(2) of the Metropolitan Washington Airports Act of 1986 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/500"},"text":"Public Law 99–500","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/1783-375"},"text":"100 Stat. 1783–375","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/591"},"text":"Public Law 99–591","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3341-378"},"text":"100 Stat. 3341–378","children":[],"tail":") is omitted as executed."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idcc6e04b0-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idcc6e04b1-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 6005(a) of the Metropolitan Washington A